Sure, here's an example of how you can use Ant Design Vue's `a-row` and `a-col`
components to create a list using a grid layout: ```vue
<template>
  <div class="breakingNews">
    <h2>Breaking News</h2>
    <a-row :gutter="10">
      <a-col :span="24">
        <a-row :gutter="10">
            test
          <a-col :span="24" v-for="(article, index) in news" :key="index">
            <a-card
              :style="{
                backgroundImage:
                  article.multimedia === null
                    ? 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15)'
                    : `url(${article.multimedia[0].url})`,
                height: '150px',
                backgroundRepeat: 'no-repeat',
                backgroundSize: 'cover',
                backgroundPosition: 'center',
                borderRadius: '8',
              }"
            >
              <a
                href="newsItem.short_url"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                <div
                  :style="{
                    backgroundImage: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7),
                    height: '150px',
                    display: 'flex',
                    borderRadius: '8',
                    alignItems: 'center',
                    textAlign: 'left',
                    p: '20px',
                  }"
                  class="news-item"
                >
                  <Heading as="h3" color="#fff"> {news.title} </Heading>
                </div>
              </a>
            </a-card>
          </a-col>
        </a-row>
      </a-col>
    </a-row>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
import { fetchNews } from "@/services/newsAPI";
import { ref } from "vue";

export default {
  setup() {
    const getNews = async () => {
      const res = await fetchNews();
      return res;
    };
    const news = ref(getNews());

    console.log(news.value);

    return {
      news,
    };
  },
};
</script>

<style scoped>
.news-item {
  width: 100%;
  height: 150px;
  background-size: cover;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-position: center;
  border-radius: 8px;
}

.news-content {
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  text-align: left;
  padding: 20px;
  border-radius: 8px;
}

.news-title {
  color: #fff;
  margin: 0;
}
</style>
``` In this example, I've used the `a-card` component from Ant Design Vue to
create each news item with a card-like layout. The news items are displayed in a
grid layout using `a-row` and `a-col` components, and the background image for
each news item is set using inline styles. The title of each news item is
displayed within the card's content area.
